metadata.name: CrossWorlds #289
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180Â°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Quasiflock #158
metadata.description:
Quasiflock is a 2022 rework of a 2006 realtime animated generative system, originally one of the projects from which later my toxiclibs library collection and some other big client projects & brand identities grew out of. The piece was part of a long, multi-year investigation into particle systems, agents and the aesthetic of fluid dynamics. Even though the approach used here is very primitive, my overall aim was to create a dynamic (and minimally interactive/responsive) system, which is above all mesmerizing to watch and somewhat feels alive. Since the original Java/Processing version isn't able to run anymore, I did some major updates and ported it to Zig & WebAssembly to give it a new life, more fluidity and a larger audience. Hope you enjoy!

10 parametric color themes (each with variations)
10 macro design/behavioral params (to control dozens more)
optionally mouse/touch responsive (rotate/pulsate)...

Made w/ Zig, WASM & thi.ng/umbrella

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #1135
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: Spark Chambers #69
metadata.description:
At the crossroads of science and art, Spark Chambers is a cosmic ray painting experience.

The first image you get is the result of the combination of spark chambers with unique design and the cosmic ray flux (the angular resolution of the cosmic ray flux is the real one). The painting is produced by the Â«Â sparksÂ Â» induced by the cosmic rays inside the spark chambers.

Different features are used to compute rarity level.

This cosmic painting can be animated (press space or left-click).
You can enjoy a never ending cosmic painting by pressing a (with change of colors, detectors, etcâ¦).

To experience Spark Chambers as a realistic cosmic ray experiment, press m and youâll enjoy the cosmic flux as you can see it in museum with real spark chambersâ¦ 
Cosmic ray flux is intense, 100 cosmic rays/m2/s at sea level !
Take some time to look at these tracks, sometimes youâll see specific nuclear interactionsâ¦. (even neutrinos like interactionsâ¦).

There are many possibilities of interaction with the token if you wish to (press h to display all the possibilities in Open Live).

In  particular you can save all the beautiful images youâll produce in high resolution press h for details).

(*) Spark chambers have been widely used at the beginning of the 19th century to study subatomic physics.  They consist in a stack of metal plates placed in a sealed box filled with a noble gas. When a charged particle from a cosmic ray travels through the box, itÂ ionises the gas between the plates. A high voltage is applied between each adjacent pair of plates before that ionisation disappears, then sparks can be made to form along the trajectory taken by the ray, and the cosmic ray in effect becomes visible as a line of sparks. Adapted from Wikipedia.

________

Price is not fixed and will change with time (down or up).
It will start as a Dutch Auction, dropping price every 5 minutes from 10 to 6 tez.
________

More informations on the project : https://sites.google.com/view/tidally-disrupted-star/spark-chambers.
________

This artwork was created using p5js, scribble, chroma-js and sweetalert2.
________

TidallyDisruptedStar (Twitter : @TidallyD). Paris. 22-2-22.

metadata.name: Euphonic #1332
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the MoirÃ© effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

The machine never sleeps.
Build. Construct. Develop. Create. Form. Produce. Generate. Repeat.

CONTROLS:
A - Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)
S - Download image
Double tap (mobile) - Download image
1-6 - Modify scale (1 = default, 2048 x 2730px, 6 = maximum, 12288 x 16380px (very performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F - Fit to current screen size
G - Toggle grain overlay
L - Toggle background grid lines

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.

metadata.name: Overshadow #4
metadata.description:
As a multitude of shadowy forms rotate around a central point, new lines, shapes, and colors emerge.  An exploration of animation, color, rotation, and opacity.

WARNING: Contains flashing images, extreme in some cases!

Press 's' to save a video.  You can choose between mp4 or gif formats, in a variety of resolutions. The time options are based around seamless points for each individual work.  There are 3 aspects of each work that change over time: Color, Size, and Rotation.  While color and individual options are seamless for that particular aspect, 'Size + Rotation' or 'Full Color + Size + Rotation' will provide the best visually seamless video (note that some works will not have a size option as they don't change in this regard).

p5js, gif.js, h264-mp4-encoder.js

metadata.name: Vistas #222
metadata.description:
Vistas is an exploration in using layers to build an abstracted geometric landscape using a generative algorithm. But in a way that not only creates a digital image but also allows for the creation of an IRL physical artwork made from the 18 layers of laser cut wood. 

All mints created in first day will receive a free physical woodcut valued at ~$250. Up to 10% of all other mints may randomly get a free physical as well. 

Learn more about physicals: https://alleditions.art/p/vistas

The canvas for each output may be one of three different orientations, a square, portrait, or landscape. The portrait and landscape orientations create physicals that are 7.5 x 11.5 inches and square orientations create 7.5 x 7.5 inch physicals. 

The resulting output is carefully designed so that it can be exploded into discreet layers (Shift-E) and exported as an SVG (Shift-S) so it can be used to laser cut or plot an IRL physical artwork. 

A variety of elements are used to construct each unique one of a kind landscape. Sun, moon, sunbeams, stars, clouds, mountains, hills, plains, beaches, fields, water, boats, rocks, trees, and even mysterious obelisks. 



UTILITY

Shift - P to export a PNG
Shift - E explode the layers
Shift - S export a vector SVG

Slide the layers with the arrow keys. Click and drag the mouse to move the light source and adjust the layer shadows.

QUERY STRINGS

Add &screws=true to render with screw holes for cutting in order to assemble a physical with chicago screws.

Adjust the size of the output by adding &x=1150 and/or &y=1150 to adjust the physical size of the output where 100 = 1 inch.
